<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880524-0021 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Mellon Bank Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MEL </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Mellon Datacenter, a unit of Mellon Bank Corp.'s Mellon Bank, said it agreed to purchase Backroom Systems Group, a developer of personal computer software that automates labor-intensive tasks for financial institutions. Terms weren't disclosed.    Both parties have agreed to the transaction, subject to the execution of a stock-purchase agreement and to federal bank regulatory approval.    Three-year-old Backroom Systems, based in Monroe, N.C., had sales last year of $3.4 million. It is the sole operating unit of Vertical Technologies Inc. Upon completion of the transaction, Backroom Systems would become a subsidiary of Pittsburgh-based Mellon Bank. </TEXT></DOC>